### Priority 3: Orchestrator

After extracting everything:
- dm_agent.py becomes an orchestrator
- It imports and coordinates the extracted modules
- Target: <800 lines

## Rules During Refactoring

### DO:

- ✅ Move code exactly as-is first
- ✅ Fix imports in all affected files
- ✅ Run tests after each move
- ✅ Commit frequently (one logical change per commit)
- ✅ Keep the same function signatures
- ✅ Document what you moved in commit messages

### DON'T:

- ❌ Rewrite logic while moving (separate refactor)
- ❌ Rename functions while moving (breaks imports)
- ❌ Move and optimize at the same time
- ❌ Skip running tests
- ❌ Make large commits with many files

## Verification Checklist

After each extraction:

```bash
# 1. Tests pass
pytest tests/ -v

# 2. Server starts
uvicorn api.main:app --port 8000

# 3. Endpoints work (manual check)
curl http://localhost:8000/health

# 4. No import errors
python -c "from api.main import app"
```

## Commit Message Format

```
refactor: extract {what} to {where}

- Move {N} endpoints from main.py to routers/{file}.py
- Update imports in {affected files}
- No logic changes

Lines changed:
- main.py: {before} -> {after} (-{diff})
- {new_file}: 0 -> {lines}
```

